Nigeria on Friday, December 25, Christmas Day, reported 712 new confirmed cases which took the country’s total to 82,747, just as the pair of Lagos and Kaduna states saw the discharge of a combined 384 persons who recovered from the virus through the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) “community recovery” programme. Community recovery means the said infected patients were managed from the point of testing positive for coronavirus through treatment and recovery by keeping them within their various homes with strict compliance to COVID-19 guidelines rather than admitting into any of the isolation centres spread across the country. The latest update from the NCDC shows that while Lagos had 248 of the 384 persons, Kaduna reported the rest of 136 persons who recovered from COVID-19 through community recoveries. EXPOSED - HOW LAGOS DOCTOR DISCOVERED MAJOR REASONS WHY MOST WIVES NOW HEAVILY CHEATS ON THEIR HUSBANDS AND THE PERMANENT SECRET TO SEXUALLY SATISFYING THEIR WIVES. DON'T BE A VICTIM! Lagos, still the epicentre of the virus in Nigeria since February 27, also recorded the highest number of new cases for the day with 388 new infections while the Federal Capital Territory (FCT) recorded 77 to emerge second. Kwara (39), Katsina (35) and Bauchi (33) are third, fourth and fifth states with the highest number of new cases for the day. 10 Die In Road Crash In Kwara Celtics Confirm Death Of 12-Time NBA Champion KC Jones According to the NCDC update gathered from 19 states and the FCT and made public via the NCDC’s verified Twitter handle, @NCDCgov, the total number of recoveries for the day is 588, taking the total discharges so far to 70,239 while the death toll reached 1,246 after four fatalities were recorded on the day. The breakdown of the latest update is as follows: 712 new cases of #COVID19Nigeria; Lagos-388 FCT-77 Kwara-39 Katsina-35 Bauchi-33 Plateau-22 Ogun-18 Akwa Ibom-16 Delta-13 Kaduna-12 Osun-12 Yobe-11 Sokoto-10 Kebbi-8 Enugu-6 Edo-5 Ondo-3 Niger-2 K